BONN , June 8 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- A large-scale joint maritime exercise involving 13 countries , either NATO member states or their Baltic partners , will be conducted in the Baltic Sea on June 11-21 , it was reported here today .
<ENAMEX TYPE="OKAY">The joint war game is reported to be the first in the region to be held by the armed forces of nations from both Eastern and Western Europe and the United States .</ENAMEX>
Russia , Poland , Latvia , Lithuania and Estonia are taking part in the exercise under the NATO 's Partnership for Peace -LRB- PFP -RRB- program .
Two German naval bases , Flensburg and Eckernfoerde , will host the maneuvers , expected to involve some 4,000 servicemen and 48 warships as well as the air forces of NATO countries .
The exercise , to be commanded by Rear Admiral Robert C. Williamson of the United States , will test the capabilities of national coast guards and marine search and salvage operations and improve coordination between the navies and air forces of the participant countries .
